{
  "texts": [
    "The base case is immediate from the definition of π in Definition 5.29.6.",
    "The ¬ and ∧ cases are also straightforward.",
    "For the □ i case, if M, X ⊮ □ i φ, then there is a Y ∈ S such that XR i Y and M, Y ⊮ φ, which with the inductive hypothesis implies θ(φ) ̸ ∈ Y, which with XR i Y implies ■ i θ(φ) ̸ ∈ X and hence θ(□ i φ) ̸ ∈ X.",
    "In the other direction, suppose θ(□ i φ) ̸ ∈ X. WhereY = {y | ■ i y ∈ X} ∪ {-θ(φ)},(5.9)suppose for reductio that [Y) is not a proper filter, i.e., ⊥ ∈ [Y).",
    "Then since {y | ■ i y ∈ X} is a filter, by (5.9) and Fact 5.30 there is a ■ i y ∈ X such that y ∧ -θ(φ) ≤ ⊥, which implies■ i y ≤ ■ i θ(φ)(5.10) by the properties of ■ i."
  ]
}